76561198135995828,Recommended,329130,30519763,Posted: 14 March,all,/*ShadowHero*/,"You can tell the developers put lots of effort into the game. It's simple to learn (although the controls are not intuitive at first, give it time), and it can be as mindless or as strategic as you want to make it. The building aspect is a simple point and click system with the ability to copy large portions, mirror them, and place on the opposite side of your ship. Space battles are just good oldfashioned blow-crap-up fun. Getting destroyed by a difficult faction or fleet just gives you motivation to improve your ship building skills and battle strategies. And the music... Absolutely immersive, and is a decent jam while blowing ships into smitherines. I highly recommend the DLC soundtrack. i cant imagine playing the game without it now that I look back. The only negative I can see to this game is the fact that it does tend to go into a lag fest when you enter a bee infested or thorn infested territory. In those situations, the lag is manageable (it feels a bit like slow mo, so get ready to fight those battles reaaally slow). Otherwise, avoid those territories and that problem never occurs. One of the reasons I bought this game is to get my spaceship building fix, while still being playable on a non-gaming laptop. Most games of that genre are highly demanding and don't run well unless you have capable hardware. If you are in a similar situation, look no farther than Reassembly. Runs nicely on crap - medium grade hardware."
