76561197999841420,Recommended,329130,14001985,"Posted: 15 January, 2015",all,Liam The Great,"This game may not look like much. Heck, there aren't even any textures, but i must say, Reassembly has quickly become one of my favorite steam games of all time.The main focus of the game is collecting resources from space plants (which seem to grow on anything that isn't constantly flying at full speed) and ships that belong to enemy factions. These resources can then be sold to friendly stations, who will not only give you credits, but also use the collected resources to build friendly ships, who in turn also collect resources to continue the cycle. Other than the initial ships in the world when you start the game, every ship, turret, and station must be spawned in from a factory (which is attached to another ship, turret, or station) when said factory has enough resources to build. All ships, plants, and debris are persistantly exsistant in the world, even when you leave the area. I cannot express in words how tantalizing the very idea of such a vast yet simple cycle is. Fortunantly, I CAN say (and with absolute certainty) that you MUST buy this game!PS: The dev team is actually active, so don't be scared of the ""early access"" label."
