,Recommended,329130,28415201,"Posted: 16 December, 2016",all,Some Guy,"Wow, I was surprised to find out that I hadn't written a review for this game yet, so here it goes:Reassembly is probably one of the most unique games I've played. Essentially, it's a top-down RTS-ish shooter game, where you get to build your ship from the ground up. This means unlimited possibilities in your playstyle, but each individual part you build can be destroyed. This means that when building you have to take into consideration the armor and placement of features on your ship.There is also a massive faction system in the game, and your whole goal is to make sure that yours prospers. This might seem tricky, but you can build and hire allies to help you out in securing more sectors of the universe. Eventually, your goal is to either take over the entire universe, or go through one of the wormholes at the center, travelling you to another universe. You can also upload your fleet that you assemble for other players to battle. The fleet you upload will appear as an ""Agent"" fleet in someone else's universe. Agents are player uploaded fleets, and there are 8 per universe, so it isn't as easy to take over the universe as it first appears.One of the most interesting and subtle features is that you areevolvingthe faction that you choose. All of the ships/stations/etc. that you create can be rebuilt by all of your allies. This doesn't seem like a very big deal, but later in the game it is. After a while of playing in the same universe, I noticed that I, singlehandedly, evolved my allegience of farmers into the most powerful fighting force in the universe. This means that you can alter the playstyle of your faction into something completely different then how they started.Something else to note is that this game is incredibly modder friendly. I had neveractuallymodded a game before I bought Reassembly. All I knew how to do was install mods that I downloaded online. However, I found that Reassembly's files were incredibly easy to navigate, and I could tell exactly what I was looking for when I saw it. All I had to do was open some files in Notepad or Notepad++, and just look around for the things I wanted changed. Again, the files are really self-explanitory.I highly recommend this game to everyone who likes top-down shooters and building games. I give it a 9/10*EDIT* I edited this review, because I feel like I didn't go into enough detail in the original one."
