,Recommended,329130,15832628,"Posted: 14 May, 2015",all,Halcyoun,"Simply put, this game is amazeballs! Seriously, buy this game. I would never have imagined someone making something like this or me going ♥♥♥♥♥♥♥ over it and yet here it is; At it's core just a handful of basic ideas, geometric building blocks, and one giant helping of awesome-sauce slathered on top to drown the whole thing in.Here's what to expect:1. A Procedurally generated space sandbox so the game is literally new every time you start a new game.2. A palette of glowing geometric blocks with which to build your epic spaceship/station heart out.3. Your own fleet lovingly mouse-crafted by you from one of 7 factions unlockable by playing the game and dominating your enemies.4. 100s of stock ships from the 12 (or 13?) distinct in-game factions populating your space-box (that's ""space sandbox"" for those of you catching up).5. One of my own ships showing up in your space-box bent on dominating your universe via the ""Wormhole"" system that allows AI controlled versions of other Reassembly player's ships to appear as ""Agents"" and lay down some good ol' fashioned obliteration on your♥♥♥♥♥6. Out of control radiant geometric space-plants growing on  nearby asteroid fields that SEEM to not pose a serious threat compared to the other guys with plasma-cannons and burst-lasers but just wait....just wait...7. Moddable factions (currently in beta) where you, yes YOU! can create your own block palette, ships, and other faction goodies to inject into your game or upload to the Steam Workshop and let others play with your wonderful (or evil...) creations.8. An awesome in-game soundtrack by recording artist Peaks.9. Hours to fly by as you have an amazing time playing one of the greatest games there ever was or is or will be in this dimension or the other infinity of them. Seriously, buy this game.What not to Expect:1. True synchronous multiplayer....sorry folks, this doesn't seem to be a thing in Reassembly but who knows about the future? *wink wink Arthur wink wink*2. Boredom. In fact, kiss that ♥♥♥♥♥♥♥ goodbye because Reassembly will be filling his usual spot from now on.3. Buyer's Remorse. ""This game is good. This is game is very good."" - Everyone"
76561197968577837,Recommended,329130,17659034,"Posted: 22 August, 2015",all,Legend,"A fun twin stick spaceship shooter with an organic feel to it similar to Pixeljunks Flow. You collect food called R(esource) and trade it for C(redits) to unlock new ship parts and raise your point allowance to stick more guns and thrusters to your ships body.Damage taken is reflected on your ships, parts are removed and will regrow fairly quickly. Half your thrusters missing on one side of your ship? Have fun trying to escape without smacking right into the next obstacle. If you command block is destroyed you respawn at the nearest factory station or ship, while losing all R. No big deal, chances are you randomly crash you ship into the next asteroid at least a couple of times.You expand territory for you faction by activating space stations and feeding them resources. Once you unlock the factory block you can start building your own fleet with your own designs, and even pop out your own stations. Massively fun for a bit but it's really a one trick pony.The goodControls are good, even though you can build clunky ships.Ship Designs are fun and designing your own fleets is quite neat.Lots of ship designs from user generated content, also workshop support now.The Organic world with it feeding and growing cycle is sweet, even if only rudimentary.Offer  at least 6-7 hours ofgoodfun. More if you enjoy the editor, optimizing fleets and trying out the different races. I doubt we see much more support from the dev that adds more replyability, but you never know.The badController support isn't complete, feels like 80% is there and the rest just never got done.Tutorial is a joke, it just checks for input and a couple of conditions, I accidently skipped almost half of it in the first 3 seconds. At the very list it needs to disable other inputs and walk you though it step by step.Simple block ship designs tend to do better than fancy. Wrong incentive.Editor has a snap function for connecting parts, nice but it only works 50% of the time making it almost useless.Some ship design are rather clunky and the AI does a good job of smashing into every solid body, Funny the first two times but it does get old really fast after that.Low replayability, the simulation aspect of the world isn't really complex enough to allow for new situations to arise.Looking forward to a sequel, I would love to see the core concepts of the game flashed out and some support for drop in multiplayer."
