,Recommended,329130,30123956,Posted: 23 February,all,Zantharan,"If you ever played games onFunorb.comand played Voidhunters, this is the game for you. It is a top down, 2D space game. You pilot a ship through the univese that you build from unlockable components, fighting off multiplle factions with their own unique ship components. when you have built your perfect fleet, you can fly through a worm hole and upload it so that it appears in someone else's game."
76561197966558357,Recommended,329130,29330938,Posted: 17 January,all,sinsro,"The game's selling point is you can build yhour own spaceships from an array of building blocks, such as a shield block, cannon block, command block, thrusters block, hull blocks and so on. It then uses a physics engine to move it about, so you need to balance the vessel well and provide enough sufficiently powered trusters in all directions to be able to move and turn.Weapon firing can be set to autotarget, so in effect you just move slowly around while your cannons destroy anything nearby so you can pick up loot that is needed for upgrades and unlocking new building blocks. Enemies will fire back and destroy your ship block by block, but after a while the blocks auto-generate.You can also build AI controlled ships, based on your own designs. Those ships can in turn build other ships, so you can dominate the galaxy quite soon. Then it is time to enter a black hole for a fresh universe, where you can start over from your current technology level.A challenge with this game is that controlling your ship is cumbersome. Even if you design it well, it will still handle sluggish, and I found myself getting stuck in space debris a lot. So, if you approach the game as an action game, it will be very irritating. Approach it more like a strategy game, and it makes more sense though.Another issue with the game, is it has quite limited scope. Once you unlock all upgrades, there is simply not much to do. You will have no use for the money you collect, and you just aimlessly float around to repeat what you did before over and over. Would be nice with some variation, and perhaps some quests. This makes the game a rather short experience.Overall, it is a fun game with some fresh innovations."
