,Recommended,329130,28781588,"Posted: 28 December, 2016",all,Melchior,"Buy this game. This is easily one of the most immediately enjoyable titles in my Steam Library. Over the 10 hours I have played Reassembly so far, it has brought me more joy and excitment than Skyrim, Fallout 4, and the Saints Row series combined. For a game that is essentially a customizable version of Asteroids, this title births a spectacular amount of content at every turn. Depending on how you choose to play, it can be a bullet hell shooter, a top-down sandbox survival, or  a space fairing cross between Terraria and an RTS. The mercifully laissez faire ship customization means that it only takes a matter of hours to get to a point where you can build your ideal spacecraft, shred a section of the star system, jump through a worm hole, and scrap your initial design to take on new, more powerful enemies. The opportunities for customization only multiply as you unlock new factions, each with their own unique powers and challenges.All of this beng said, the game isn't without a few technical flaws, the main issues involving communication between local save data and the Steam Cloud. Though it is totally possible to save all progress on your personal computer, after a successful initial run, I have found it completely impossible to start the game through Steam or get it to synchronize with subscribed workshop content...not that the game needs any of that, frankly. However, the issue stands as a glaring flaw in an otherwise wonderful game."
