76561198056253064,Recommended,329130,14657470,"Posted: 25 February, 2015",all,TRITIUMNITR0X,"Props to the developer.Reassembly is a well-put together, astonishingly beautiful game in it's simplicity. It's music is calming, the gameplay is smooth (aside from the problems -list to follow), and it's very interesting in the way that the factions each have their own preferred ship pieces. Command Mode is very interesting, and I would love to see an ability to command ships and assign Generals who Command their ships under your order. As well, the ability to force all currently active ships to change to the ship you want, and the ability to force all your Stations to spawn your preferred ships (because flying to each ship/station to edit them individually is impossible), would be great.However, aside from the positive, Reassembly suffers from a few issues that are not just annoying, but are also game-breaking. They aren't too common to come across, but you will find them at some point.These problems are:1) Losing an entire fleet, which you've spent hours building up, in an instant. This needs to be changed. Reassmbly shouldn't just be about grinding for R (Resources), it should be about building fleets and going into enemy territory to conquer them.2) Conquering fleets is great, but what of conquering sectors of space? Hours have been spent flying through a sector and murdering countless fleets only to then have realized that that single sector is still not conquered.3) A.I.'s spawn kill users, especially if there are enough powerful enemy ships around. We are not given a buffer time to escape from numerous enemies lingering all over the Stations (when we're spawned in, they just annihilate us in seconds). This problem is infuriating, especially after just Starting up the game from a save and 10 enemies are literally sitting there, waiting for the user. A way to fix this issue (if not to give the user a buffer time) would be to check for the time in which it took for a player to get murdered after their last death, and if it's a very short period of time between deaths, the player should be spawned at a Station a few clicks away.If you play the game for long enough, you'll experience these issues and side with my opinion that the game needs these fixes as soon as possible.But again, this game is amazing. I would definately recommend it!"
