76561198048112885,Recommended,329130,17607398,"Posted: 18 August, 2015",all,Higsmoid,"This game is almost perfect.I just bought this game today but I've already had my share of experiences. The tutorial was a bit meh but after I got to the point where I could start exploring, the world opened up to me. While I wish that there was a little bit of written lore (an update would be nice!), the lore is almost self-explanatory simply based on what a faction's ships *do*. The mind wanders just you yourself wander, trying to infer whatever you can about this colorful, geometric universe.The combat is good and the physics behind movement take a bit of getting used to. This game isn't as much about that, though. It's all about building your perfect modular ship. Currently I am rocking a missile dreadnaught, though it has a few weaknesses. There is no *best* kind of ship in the game.I would highly reccomend this game, and would urge anyone to buy it even if it's not on sale.Now, as for things that could directly be improved upon (either through modding, updates, or hell, I'm so pleased with the game I'd pay for DLC) I'd like to see even more modules (sometimes I feel like I want even bigger guns) more factions (I want to see more cool and outlandish ideas that either impressed upon me a sense of wonder or terror), and story-mode/objectives (Some kind of diplomacy or even flavor text would be a nice addition to the game). This would be the first game that I would have liked to have still been in early-access because of the idea of even more content, instead of groaning. And believe me, I know how bad it gets; I bought towns ;-;"
