76561198261808995,Recommended,329130,21596726,"Posted: 2 March, 2016",all,MIYUKI,"Played this game for many hours outside of steam. This game is quite enjoyable, relaxing experience. Take your time to build ships however you want for whatever roles are needed - go out and expand your territory, or if you are like me and favor the Farmer faction simply populate surfaces with plants and watch as your fleet size grows. Of the very few down sides to this game is a lack of detailed instructions on the part functions ingame (you basically have to memorize them, learn from guides and videos posted by others). Some in-game mechanics are also lacking documentation (such as how to restrict building of ships). All the lack of documentation issues generally don't add up to much problem once you have played a faction for some time however.Overall a very good game and an enjoyable experience. Definitely worth the purchase if you like building stuff and seeing how well it performs."
