76561198109752549,Recommended,329130,22489775,"Posted: 17 April, 2016",all,drodig63,"Reassembly is a game that takes place in a genre of space games that allows you to create your own ships and use them to fight other ships. The main difference is, Reassembly does this is a very unique and different way. You have full control of what you ship, or station, will look like, except for the manditory command module. You can use a variety of parts for all of the playable factions and many modded factions. You can build a fleet to your specifications and can use it to conquer the entire universe that was generated for your faction to reside in. Each faction has its own special parts with their own specifications aswell as their own types of weaponry.(Note: These numbers I am using are not based on faction id's in the Sandbox.)WARNING: SOME PEOPLE MAY CONSIDER THIS NEXT PART AS A HUGE SPOILER. DO NOT READ IF KNOWING THIS INFORMATION SPOILS THE GAME FOR YOU.Faction 1 ""The Terrans: The starting faction, it is very well balanced and generally simple to use. Faction 2 ""The Farmers"": Largest variety in parts, this faction tends to behave neutrally, but can be very deadly later on. This faction is known for its seed planter. Faction 3 ""The Reds"": This faction has the weakest hull armor. They do however, have the most parts on their ships, due to their blocks not being able to scale. This faction also tends to have the most weapons on their ships, and very good point defense. Faction 4 ""The Tinkrell"": This faction has customizable weaponry, making them have the ability to obtain the most powerful weapons in the game. Faction 5 ""The Crystalline ships"": This faction has very strong hull armor and some of the most powerful plasma cannons in the game. Faction 6 ""The bees"": This faction has very powerful lasers, and the most powerful thrusters in the game. Faction 7 ""The Sentinels"": This faction is well know for its nukes and obliterator burst lasers, a certain type of part can even used for melee damage.Pros:-Massive level of creativity able to be put into your playthrough.-Many ways to play.-Variety of factions to play as.-Many ships to fight.-Very active workshop.-Great community and fan base.Cons:-Their is a P limit based on the command module, amount of thrusters, and amount of weapons the ship has.-Their is a block limit based on the amount of blocks your ship has.Reassembly tends to the needs of players who like combat, building, or both. Their are many different ways to fight, just like their are many different ways to build."
