,Recommended,329130,16747712,"Posted: 27 June, 2015",all,R4Z0RW1R3,"I must say, I don't come back to games that often.But this is one of those gems that I can't leave alone for longer than a week or so, it's a masterpiece.The idea? Make a ship, blow up other ships, farm resources, make an army, use the aforementioned army to destroy other ships and make your faction inevitably powerful and build super destroyers, for the sake of entertainment.But it's so much more than that, it has beautiful graphics (even on lower settings), doesn't destroy your framerate, allows free building of pretty much whatever you want, in terms of ships / stations, the only part of this game that I feel is lacking is in both the modding and sandbox areas.They could use a little work, not for me, but for those inexperienced in the usage of command lines.Aside from that, if you like action/exploration, then take up this game, i've had 90+ hours on it and I'm still not bored.^^"
,Recommended,329130,16488035,"Posted: 17 June, 2015",all,A Trikicat,"If you're a sucker for design-it-and-fail kind of games (like I am), then this game will be the crack to your addiction. The simplistic parts that you get to design your ship with is all you need to create the coolest looking space-ships this side of the galaxy. It's not as simple as ""plug the device on and go"", you need to build your ship CORRECTLY or it won't maneuver through space! Don't have enough retro-thrusters? You better hope you can back off the enemy fast enough by turning (and not dying from losing your back end). Didn't think you needed thrusters to turn? Guess you're going in one direction infinitely. It's a constant failure zone, and I just LOVE IT!It's a very grindy game, so if you don't like grinding, I would certainly stay away. And the sandbox mode isn't very intuitive either. I tried to build something in the constructor (in the sandbox mode), and I didn't even get things to build with. Don't get fooled with sandbox mode, it isn't a free build-any-ship-for-free mode @.@ If you don't mind grinding as you play different factions (have to unlock them), then you'll find HOURS upon HOURS trying new designs and seeing if they stack up with the best.24 hours of Gameplay later:This game is even better!  Again the game is grindy, but the different factions (without mods) force you to build your ships in different patterns. Have a good design for faction 1 (Terrans)? You're not using it on Faction 4 because there are no long-triangle blocks! The only downside with ship-building, is when you test your ship against others' you need to fight these really cheap min-maxed ships that do nothing but fly backwards when your ship catches up with every default ship in the game; actually it's the CPU attacking the other ships, but it's still cheap tactics that win.Also, the sandbox mode isn't as convoluted as I first thought. I can create any ship I want with the right commands, and even see the default ship palettes for each faction. Unfortunately this isn't explained very well and you need a tutorial outside of the game to understand which commands do what (and that Faction 1 is actually Faction 8 for example). You can still build any ship you want in your save game, but the sandbox is very misleading (not much of a sandbox :/ More of a programmer's blank sheet of paper). I'm still getting my money's worth out of the game; Time to conquer the galaxy!"
,Recommended,329130,16652556,"Posted: 23 June, 2015",all,Narnach,"I started playing and before I knew it, 5 hours had passed. This game is fun & addictive. It's a strange mix between bullet hell shooters, real-time strategy and Spore (the species evolution game).Build & customize your ship, research new building blocks, add on a factory, start producing ships for your fleet, build space stations, conquer the map. This last bit... tough!The ship builder/designer is a game unto itself. Construct a ship by taking your command module and attaching blocks to it. Armor blocks, engines, power generators, harvesters, automated turrets, manual fire weapons, missile launchers, drone launchers, etc. Then press the test button and watch the AI duke it out in an arena against 5 different ships with similar construction cost in 1 vs 1 battles. It will highlight strengths & weaknesses... and it'll give you more information on how to further tweak the perfect ship.I think I spent over half of my time with this game in the ship builder and battle simulator. It's just so much fun!"
