,Recommended,329130,16561737,"Posted: 20 June, 2015",all,Braedon,"Reassembly is a 2D vector graphics based space shooter where the only objective is to conquer and destroy everything else. You start in a small ship in your own faction with only one station to your name. You gain resources by destroying enemy faction ships, collecting resources from nearby asteroids, and expanding your territory by activating unused stations. Once you have enough resources, you can design your very own ships to the fullest degree as they are no mandatory templates or spaceship hulls to work off of. You can build ships that can build other ships on the fly and command a fleet of your custom made ships. All the blocks that make up a ship must be researched first, and the only way to gain blocks to your ""datastore"" is to destroy enemy ships with said block.*** Pros ***Vector graphics and particle effects mean zero load times and small game size (~100 MB)Custom build all ships from movement to weapon systemsExtensive tutorial to teach the games mechanicsHigh replayability as you can unlock other factions shipsGood soundtrack and sound effects*** Cons ***Large battles can get confusing because of particle effects"
,Recommended,329130,16513919,"Posted: 18 June, 2015",all,Demon Cleaner,"The game I've been looking for. Reassembly is easy to understand, rough to master, with multiple different ship construction strategies that may or may not work, whether alone or together.Your objective is to collect resources to upgrade and build your ship(s), eventually providing your ship with a factory block that can spawn a fleet for you. Enemies are generated off of other players' designs, copied through the use of wormholes, keeping you however from ever encountering real players, just AI versions of their fleets.Pros:-No frame drops, I've rarely been lowered in video quality throughout my time playing-Expansive maps, plenty of sectors generated swiftly with new stations to capture and factions to fight-Comfortable building interface, with useful tools like mirror and copy and paste to make everything much faster to build, putting you in the fight sooner, plus a lot of weapons and tools to make specialized ships like drone swarm spawners, rocket carronades, snipers, etc.-Nice artstyle. Very minimalistic, but it is still nonetheless fun to watch your ships ""reassemble"" as the new parts are traced and come to life in the middle of a battle-No loading screens. Literally none.-Test feature, which pits your newly made ship against another of the same value to test its strength in a real battle, before you try and fly a space dumpster into a battle and waste timeCons:-Slightly repetitive soundtrack. Good music, but it seems to loop a lot. Maybe I'm just playing too much :P-Instructions and controls must be looked up a couple times to learn how to do everything (ie Toggle hud, commision fleet ships, set child cycles for your fleet's ships, etc)-My biggest problem: Ship control. Most games like this have the WASD keys stay in a locked position of North, West, South, East. This game, however, orients control around your crosshair, meaning you have to constantly check which way your shape is facing and reorient yourself to fly properly. Very hard to get used to.All in all, I'm giving it a 8/10. Fantastic game, and I highly recommend it, I would just like to see some new features implemented and that movement control thing given a second option.Things I want to See Implemented:-Co-op multiplayer. Allow a friend to join you in your faction and grow alongside you. Perhaps a combining force of an intelligent gunship and bot spawning mother-ship, I thought this would make a fantastic duo.-New music-New weapons and hull parts/utillity pieces, some ideas are:> Repair drone. Accelerates rebuild speed.> Cloaking system> Repulsion/Attraction blocks, for pulling in enemies into short range weapons or pushing them away from a long range ship> Kamikazee drones. Name says it all> Barrier construction. Some kind of attachment that uses resources to build walls for defense, or maybe even dispense some kind of acid or magma to ward off pursuers.> Parasite drone. A drone that embeds into the core of a ship and changes its faction, rebuilding it and putting it in your fleet, maybe even copying the schematic into your inventorySo those are my ideas and reviews of the game, hope it helped and you agree!"
