,Recommended,329130,20274082,"Posted: 3 January, 2016",all,Wutnold124,"Reassembly, at first glance and without watching the trailer/gameplay, seems like a Captain Forever (i think that's what it's called) rip-off. It's not. You aren't limited to trying to destroy the enemy core ASAP to save it's pieces so you can upgrade your ship, although you pretty much have to kill in order to upgrade your ship in the first place in Reassembly. It's pretty much just Asteroids but with badass looking ships instead of a dinky triangle. It's kinda hard to explain, but basically there are multiple factions, around 15 at the time of me writing this review, and you only get to be in one at the start. To get in others, you have to kill giant murder machines from other factions to unlock them. There's also a weird credits and resource system, you gain resource (called R in-game) by either farming or murdering other factions, and you get credits (called C in-game) by dropping off your resource at stations or ships with a factory on it, and then those stations/ships can use your resource you dropped off to make more ships, possibly a ship with a factory on it, making a weird cycle.Also, pro-tip for newbies, GET THE FARMER FACE (faction 2) AS FAST AS POSSIBLE.It's pretty much better than all of the other factions, because they can farm with ease because they can attach plants to themselves so you can essentially farm on the go, which, as previously stated, gives you resource.All in all, if you like ship building and somewhat intense space battles, Reassembly is for you. A solid 10/10."
