76561198031260818,Recommended,329130,19983206,"Posted: 26 December, 2015",all,greatorder,"I'll give this game a tentative thumbs up. It's fun, the UI isn't too bad, it's nice creating ships where you have to worry about thruster position, centre of mass (both easily done with a symmetrical ship), if the ship has enough thrusters to maintain a decent speed (space friction is in effect here) or rotate rapidly enough (my main issue when designing). But then once all is said and done there's an issue: Once you get good enoguh at ship design and you've tried it with all the factions (or all the ones you like) there's nothing to really do. The starting grind is boring, running around demolishing every AI ship, agent or not, is boring. One well designed ship helmed by a player can and will crap on everything.I feel one thing this game needs is a true multiplayer to keep it fresh for longer. As it stands, once you have a death ship (my antimatter dreadnought comes to mind) there's no way in hell anything is ever gonna kill you. Tournament mode, this game's ""multiplayer"", is pretty boring. It's two player made ships fighting, but nobody has control of them, you have to hand it over to the♥♥♥♥♥♥poor AI that seem to have two modes: 'I have drones so run away and launch them', or 'CHAAAAAAAAAAAAAAARGE!', which managed to lead to the aforementioned dreadnought getting demolished because it refused to stay at maximum range where it wouldn't get chewed up by lasers and the like.Anyway, getting back to my point, multiplayer would really benefit it. A proper multiplayer in the proper game, not some multiplayer tournament-style thing. Teams or against would be personal preference because that would give an actual challenge once you get past that critical point of 'every AI ship is killed in moments'Yes, I know that multiplayer would require a lot of work, but it feels like a game that *really* needs it. It seems almost designed for it, but it just doesn't have it."
