,Recommended,329130,29120721,Posted: 8 January,all,Robo7988143,"Reassembly is a sandbox game about building your own ships in SPACE and fighting enemies and controlling there sectors. Now to my serious review.I played over 31.2 hours and I have discovered lots of cool things about it, like uploading your fleet so it will become a agent and attack other Player's worlds when they either start a new world or go to another. Another cool thing I witnessed is that the Ship Costumization is so simple and you can costumize it 100%, Block Limits is the part I don't like about ship costumization, you cannot create extremely huge ships because of this. Another one is that your enemies will continue to grow, everytime you remove parts or add in new parts to your ship, your enemies will know this and evolve there ships to something stronger, even that one Red Faction you thought was extremely weak but later they evolved and can pack a punch to any other faction. The one thing I really hate about Reassembly is your allies. You're allies won't do anything. They just waste there time, sitting around in there bases, patrolling it and not attacking or exploring other sectors of the map, which I strongely hate. Not only that, the enemy AI also seems to suffer this as well, with this, you feel like you're the only one in the whole map exploring while others are just sitting and spending there rest of there time in there bases, flying aimlessly and then wait until getting recruited. Now that I finished gathering up all the things I know and loved and possbily strongely hate about, I made a list.ProsShip Costumization: Extremely good, giving you 99% freedom creating your own ships, but where brick limits come in, stopping you from creating a massive ship or even a gigantic station.The AI: The AI can be smart but extremely stupid at times. The only thing the AI actually knows about is attacking there enemies, gathering resources and heading back to there bases for ressupply in order to create more ships, and the new ships go on and on with gathering resources, bringing it back and create new ships, this is a endless cycle. I was hoping for them to attack your sectors or attack other sectors and spawn stations there, at most of the time in my opinion, I think there very dumb.Graphics: The Graphics are nice, when you shoot, the laser particles, missiles and drone particles show very well, even the particales thrusters make, are extremely nice, though there are a few mods on the Workshop to make it better, but at vanilla-balanced they look a little nice, looks epic when a couple of ships fight each other but that's rarely the case because the AI.The Map: The map is extremely huge, big enough for you to explore, may take up to five months to explore the whole map. The map has a bunch of living inhabitants, including your allies. The Map also haves asteriods, plants, spikey plants and other special factions that might find and destroy you. I'd say the map is epic and suitable for a exploration game.Updates: This game rarely gets updated, and may never get updated again by the developers. Updates are extremely rare for this game, and you may or may not have seen ""Reassembly updating"" or anything like that. Don't buy this game if you don't like very inactive Developers or like this game in it's current state.From what I know for the ending of this review, I'd say I recommend this. To those who like the game in it's current state with extremely inactive developers."
